Cape Town International Airport is preparing to jump-start the Western Cape's tourism industry again. Courtesy of #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Cape Town International Airport is preparing to jump-start the Western Cape's tourism industry again. It's one of three airports that will be allowed to receive international tourists from October. READ:Â Domestic flights approved for 11 more airports The airport has adopted a number of methods to reduce the risk of COVID-19. There are screens to provide information on COVID-19 containment measures, thermal screeners, social distancing, and adapted training for airport staff. Western Cape Economic Opportunities MEC David Maynier said, "we are going to be looking at potential in source markets other than our traditional source markets, particularly in the source markets in the regions which all the evidence suggests is great potential for the Western Cape." - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.